data.text:
Channing Frye - Points

Channing Frye scores a career high 33 points (2011)

On April 11, 2011, Channing Frye set his career high in points in a NBA game. That day he scored 33 points in Phoenix's home win against Minnesota, 135-127. He also had 4 rebounds, 1 assist. He shot 3/4 from two, 9/14 from three, shooting at 66.7% from the field.

Channing Frye - Rebounds

Channing Frye grabs a career high 16 rebounds (2011)

On December 30, 2011, Channing Frye tied his career high in rebounds in a NBA game. That day he grabbed 16 rebounds in Phoenix's road win against New Orleans, 78-93. He also had 10 points, 2 assists and 3 blocks.

Channing Frye - Assists

Channing Frye gives a career high 7 assists (2012)

On January 13, 2012, Channing Frye tied his career high in assists in a NBA game. That day he dished 7 assists in Phoenix's home loss against New Jersey, 103-110. He also had 15 points, 6 rebounds.

Channing Frye - Steals

Channing Frye has a career high 4 steals (2010)

On January 05, 2010, Channing Frye tied his career high in steals in a NBA game. That day he reached 4 steals in Phoenix's road win against Sacramento, 109-113. He also had 17 points, 7 rebounds.

Channing Frye - Blocks

Channing Frye blocks a career high 7 shots (2005)

On February 17, 2005, Channing Frye set his career high in blocks in a NCAA game. That day he went for 7 blocks in Arizona Wildcats's home win against Oregon Ducks, 92-67. He also had 19 points, 5 rebounds and 2 assists.
